media:group.media:title: Mga bangus sa ilang palaisdaan sa Dagupan City nagkakamatayan
media:group.media:description: Paliwanag ng Bureau of Fisheries and Aquatic Resources, nakaapekto sa mga palaisdaan ang biglang pagbabago ng temperatura ng tubig kaya naghingalo ang mga isda.

entry.title: Police to sue foreign resident who allegedly defied quarantine rules in Makati subdivision

media:group.media:title: Police to sue foreign resident who allegedly defied quarantine rules in Makati subdivision
media:group.media:description: Makati police are set to file charges against a foreign resident of an exclusive village for disobeying authorities who were enforcing the enhanced community quarantine (ECQ).

entry.title: Lung Center starts plasma therapy for COVID-19 patients

media:group.media:title: Lung Center starts plasma therapy for COVID-19 patients
media:group.media:description: The Lung Center of the Philippines said Monday it had started using plasma treatment for patients with severe symptoms of coronavirus disease (COVID-19).

entry.title: Former Tourism Secretary Ramon Jimenez Jr. passes away

media:group.media:title: Former Tourism Secretary Ramon Jimenez Jr. passes away
media:group.media:description: Former Tourism Secretary Ramon Jimenez, who started the "It's More Fun in the Philippines" campaign passed away on Monday, his family said. His death was unrelated to COVID-19, his family said in a statement.

entry.title: About 100 Filipinos in virus-hit Italy want to go home: envoy

media:group.media:title: About 100 Filipinos in virus-hit Italy want to go home: envoy
media:group.media:description: More or less 100 Filipinos in Italy, among those hardest hit by the novel coronavirus pandemic, expressed desire to join the government's repatriation program, an envoy of Manila said Monday.

entry.title: NBI investigates death of woman from childbirth after being refused by hospitals

media:group.media:title: NBI investigates death of woman from childbirth after being refused by hospitals
media:group.media:description: Presidential Spokesman Harry Roque said Justice Secretary Menardo Guevarra had assured him of an investigation into the death of a woman due to childbirth complications after she was refused by hospitals, as well as the filing of charges if necessary. In a text message to ABS-CBN News, Guevarra said the National Bureau of Investigation began looking into the incident Monday.

entry.title: 5 Filipinos in Saudi die due to COVID-19: envoy | ABS-CBN News

media:group.media:title: 5 Filipinos in Saudi die due to COVID-19: envoy | ABS-CBN News
media:group.media:description:
Five Filipinos in Saudi Arabia have died due to the new coronavirus disease, Philippine Ambassador Adnan Alonto said Monday. The 5 are among the 119 Filipinos in the Middle East kingdom that have contracted the respiratory disease, Alonto told a press briefing aired by state broadcaster PTV.

entry.title: 'It's propaganda': Iisang Dagat song earns thousands of dislikes - analyst | ANC

media:group.media:title: 'It's propaganda': Iisang Dagat song earns thousands of dislikes - analyst | ANC
media:group.media:description:
MANILA - A song released by the Chinese Embassy in Manila and performed by Filipina "jukebox queen" and Camarines Sur vice-governor Imelda Papin and other singers has earned more than 100,000 dislikes on YouTube for being a piece of propaganda for Beijing, a maritime law expert said.
